From 5031d17b0a9643db1461248ae88339508879a0d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ashokkumarkannan1 <akannan@tenstorrent.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 19:27:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Port BEVFusion to CPU-only inference

Patch 13 files to enable full Camera+LiDAR fusion inference on CPU
without CUDA. Key changes:

- setup.py: conditionally skip CUDA-only C++ extensions on CPU builds
- ops/spconv/ops.py: pure-Python CPU fallbacks for sparse conv
- ops/bev_pool/bev_pool.py: scatter_add-based CPU BEV pooling
- ops/voxel/voxelize.py: pure-Python voxelization replacing buggy C++ CPU path
- ops/iou3d/iou3d_utils.py: CPU NMS and IoU fallbacks
- ops/roiaware_pool3d/points_in_boxes.py: CPU fallbacks for point-in-box
- ops/__init__.py: graceful try/except for all unbuilt C++ extensions
- spconv/functional.py: conditional torch.cuda.amp import
- models/vtransforms: conditional autocast, fix depth_lss signatures
- models/backbones/radar_encoder.py: optional flash_attn import
- core/bbox/structures/base_box3d.py: optional iou3d_cuda, CPU overlap
- tools/test_cpu.py: minimal CPU inference test script

Tested: full forward pass with pretrained checkpoint on CPU.
